    "creation_date" : 1594891471,
    "answer_id" : 62931536,
    "question_id" : 41700798,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You must have the Gradle wrapper available locally before using <em>gradlew</em>. To construct that</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-bash prettyprint-override\"><code>gradle wrapper # --gradle-version v.xy\n</code></pre>\n<p>Optionally, pass the Gradle version explicitly. This step produces the <em>gradlew</em> binary. And then you should be able to</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-bash prettyprint-override\"><code>./gradlew build\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 18828709,
      "reputation" : 323,
      "user_id" : 13733008,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gha66_1VlUWGe3g5mQVjw3Xmf4ahrFsvd8J6TevhA=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "Nikhil Jain",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13733008/nikhil-jain"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1676957249,
    "last_edit_date" : 1676957249,
    "creation_date" : 1637227731,
    "answer_id" : 70017378,
    "question_id" : 41700798,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Instead of <code>gradlew assembleRelease</code>, use <code>./gradlew assembleRelease</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 228567,
      "reputation" : 4123,
      "user_id" : 490953,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 70,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2405c3bc16518435072748071e922040?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "maddy",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/490953/maddy"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1676957394,
    "last_edit_date" : 1676957394,
    "creation_date" : 1639120588,
    "answer_id" : 70300939,
    "question_id" : 41700798,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Issue: Couldn't find gradlew at path jenkins</p>\n<p>In my case, within the Jenkins <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continuous_integration\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">CI</a> for flutter project, I have to first run the <code>flutter build</code> app command, and then it automatically generated a <em>gradlew</em> file. And the above issue is resolved.</p>\n<p>I put this command in my Jenkins file:</p>\n<pre><code>flutter build apk\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 10793413,
      "reputation" : 111,
      "user_id" : 7940063,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://graph.facebook.com/10154239001851184/picture?type=large",
      "display_name" : "Gurminder Kaler",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7940063/gurminder-kaler"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1676957441,
    "last_edit_date" : 1676957441,
    "creation_date" : 1641695868,
    "answer_id" : 70638026,
    "question_id" : 41700798,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you are trying to run this command for a Flutter app, then go to the <em>android</em> folder first by <em>cd android</em>. And then use the command, and it should work.</p>\n<pre><code>cd android\n./gradlew signingReport\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6532405,
      "reputation" : 137,
      "user_id" : 5053142,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-qsA0o5ndh00/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACg/rIlGPZgjD30/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Ajay Menon",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5053142/ajay-menon"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1676957532,
    "last_edit_date" : 1676957532,
    "creation_date" : 1643308359,
    "answer_id" : 70883938,
    "question_id" : 41700798,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had to do <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unix2dos\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>dos2unix *</code></a> in my current folder to make it work.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 15254452,
      "reputation" : 2168,
      "user_id" : 11006729,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/9gCxl.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Florian K",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/11006729/florian-k"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1676957623,
    "last_edit_date" : 1676957623,
    "creation_date" : 1652092538,
    "answer_id" : 72170615,
    "question_id" : 41700798,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In a Flutter project, don't forget to go to 'android' folder with 'cd android'.\nThen you can run a command like './gradlew build' or './gradlew clean' on it (macOS).</p>\n"
  }, {
