    "creation_date" : 1674665269,
    "answer_id" : 75237241,
    "question_id" : 41700798,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h3>Ubuntu</h3>\n<p>Error:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Command 'gradlew' not found, did you mean: <br />\ncommand 'gradle' from snap gradle (7.2) <br />\ncommand 'gradle' from deb gradle (4.4.1-13) <br />\nSee 'snap info ' for additional versions.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Use this command:</p>\n<pre><code>./gradlew signingReport\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1628102,
      "reputation" : 5215,
      "user_id" : 1503163,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c849158de87c316eccc01649e521374a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Sanjay Bharwani",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1503163/sanjay-bharwani"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1721050404,
    "last_edit_date" : 1721050404,
    "creation_date" : 1720795666,
    "answer_id" : 78740984,
    "question_id" : 41700798,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In github action, use <a href=\"https://github.com/gradle/gradle-build-action\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://github.com/gradle/gradle-build-action</a></p>\n<pre><code>  - name: Setup Gradle\n    uses: gradle/actions/setup-gradle@v3\n</code></pre>\n<p>And then use job which needs gradle.</p>\n<p>Another important issue was, in the <strong>android</strong> folder, there was a .gitignore file with below entries</p>\n<pre><code>/gradlew\n/gradlew.bat\n</code></pre>\n<p>Hence gradlew executable was not part of the checked out code in github actions.</p>\n<p>Solution is to remove the entries from <code>.gitignore</code> and commit. Also ensure you have an entry <code>!gradle-wrapper.jar</code> to not exclude gradle-wrapper.jar as all jar files are excluded by default.</p>\n"
  } ],
  "owner" : {
    "account_id" : 9495696,
    "reputation" : 2781,
    "user_id" : 7411646,
